comments.body: @kelea99 thanks for your feedback!  We made those changes; could you please take another look at https://catalog-qa.princeton.edu/?

@sandbergja , using Coin:6521 as a control again, and everything looks exactly like what was signed off on from Alan!! I did a selective search of other coins and weird things I found (ex: Reverse Attributes
    [m4769.jpg, monogram](https://catalog-qa.princeton.edu/?f[issue_reverse_attributes_s][]=m4769.jpg%2C+monogram) ), are in the metadata within figgy itself, so orangelight is reflecting exactly what was entered.  Also, are things going to not be hyperlinked in the final option? It is not clear to me why everything field is a hyperlink.  I think this is ready to show to the stakeholder for final review, if you all are comfortable!  Great job!
@kelea99: thank you for the review!  Happy to hyperlink or de-hyperlink any fields that need it -- let me know which ones.  Yes, please feel free to show it to the stakeholder.

Fantastic! I am reaching out to Alan first thing tomorrow. I do not understand why the hypelinks are all there, because they to not seem to be linking to anything but the coin record again. but I will continue looking
